result.formatted_address: 33號 Wai Yip St, Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: TeaWood Taiwanese Cafe & Restaurant

reviews.text:
Quality is far worse than 1 year ago! We have been eating here for few years back then and loved their food. I doubt they have changed their management into some kind of profit-oriented management who don't care about the quality. Generally what I observe today is:
- removed the queuing machine/system into manually by staff marking on a BLANK paper....
- staffs became rude and we heard them yelling and swearing to colleagues right in front of us
- food quality significantly dropped, the fried chicken far thinner than before, the old menu's pasta is gone, we tried the new menu's pasta, it is disastrous. 
- price goes up to hkd 75 per dish while portion and quality goes down
All in all, it is a result of profit oriented management took over a well established brand. We will try their cwb branch one last time to see if it is the branch or the management problem.
Taste good, easy to find the table
Nice Taiwanese soup options. The deep fried chicken is always just a bit too oily though. Good fruit tea options are available too.

The oyster and seafoods soup was uniquely fulfilling coz it has RICE in it... Service was good and table was available coz we were there earlier than others b4 lunchtime.. Spoon was uniquely shaped like a shovel so 😀... Great desserts and the menu was like a storybook-so fantasy-like that was so refreshing. minced pork was tasty...
Good food. I really like the desserts.

result.name: 茶木 · 台式休閒餐廳

reviews.text: 上菜快，味道不錯，價錢略貴唔抵食。醉雞竟然係熱的。。。
冰淇淋芒果吐司好味，食到後面有d滯，兩個人下午茶點了一客，兩杯飲品，和鹽酥雞粒，夠晒皮。鹽酥雞一般。
很喜歡德福分店的紅豆苧圓，有水準！
